# <type>(<scope>): [TICKET-ID] <description>


# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (refactoring code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc)
#    perf     (performance improvements)
#    ci       (CI/CD changes)
#    build    (changes to build system or dependencies)
# --------------------
# Remember to:
#    - Use imperative mood (e.g., "add" not "added")
#    - Don't end the subject line with a period
#    - Capitalize the description
#    - Keep first line under 50 characters if possible
# --------------------
# Examples:
#    feat(api): [STUDL-123] add user authentication endpoint
#    fix(ui): [STUDL-456] resolve button alignment on mobile
#    docs(readme): [STUDL-789] update installation instructions
# --------------------
# Alternative format:
#    STUDL-123: add user authentication endpoint
# --------------------
